  "critical": false,
  "description": "Statistical process control, inspection sampling, and defect analysis for manufacturing yield optimization. Spans control charts (X-bar/R, p, c), process capability indices (Cpk/Ppk targets ≥1.33), acceptance sampling (AQL, MIL-STD-105E), FMEA, and yield modeling (Murphy's, Seeds). Semiconductor yield runs 60-90% for mature nodes and below 50% for leading edge — quality control is the difference between profit and loss. Internal organizing axis: functional (capabilities grouped by QC function: statistical monitoring, inspection, defect root-cause analysis).",
